April Issue of "Juche Idea" Published in Japan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- The April issue of "Juche Idea", the organ of the National Liaison Council of the Japan Society for Study of Kim Jong Il's Works, was published.
 It carried an article introducing the activities of the academic circle of Japan for the study of the Juche idea and book "Kim Jong Il Biography" published by the International Institute of Juche Idea and the gist of a report titled "On the significance of activities of the society for study of the Juche idea and its role" delivered by the secretary general of the Japan Society for Study of Kimilsungism at a seminar held in Osaka, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Edited there is a photo-accompanied report on the DPRK visit by the Japanese delegation for the study of the Juche Idea headed by the secretary general of the Kanagawa, Japan, Society for Study of Kim Jong Il's Works. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the report the members of the delegation expressed their will to strive for the normalization of the Japan-DPRK relations, noting that quite contrary to what media of Japan reported, the DPRK is the country where all servicepersons and people are single-mindedly united around their leader and replete with national pride. They also pointed out that the DPRK is the country where people help and lead each other forward with loving care, a country which is attaching importance to education and defending peace by standing up firm against the U.S. pressure with the Songun politics.

Radical Improvement of Inter-Korean Relations Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- There is a growing danger of a nuclear war against the north by foreign forces in Korea. This makes it incumbent upon the north and the south of Korea to boldly dispel the outdated idea of confrontation and earnestly promote the improvement of the relations through practical measures in order to defend the destiny of the nation and achieve common prosperity.
 Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in its signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the realistic way for the radical improvement and development of the inter-Korean relations for the north and the south to recognize and respect each other's ideology and system in the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration and take practical measures to this end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There have been different ideologies and systems in the north and the south for decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ignorance of the essence of the matter to argue that mutual exchange will lead to confidence building. One of the factors standing in the way of the development of the inter-Korean relations is the pattern of thinking originating from different ideologies and systems and legal and institutional problems resulting from them. Under this condition it is the best cure for the development of the inter-Korean relations to recognize the reality and respect each other's ideology and system.
 For a dramatic turn in the inter-Korean relations through the recognition and respect of each other's ideology and system, the ideas and practices of the old era of confrontation must be abandoned and all the anti-reunification institutional barriers such as the "National Security Law" repressing the desire for national reconciliation, unity and reunification through alliance with the north be pulled down in south Korea. 
 Recognition and respect of each other's ideology and system and reconciliation based on it are, indeed, the bed-rock point of principle of practical significance in the development of the inter-Korean relations. The earliest possible solution to this matter is an urgent task that brooks no further delay for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the accomplishment of the cause of independent reunification. Depending on it is whether the inter-Korean relations enter the stage of fundamental development, braving the challenges and obstructions of the foreign forces, or fall into the crisis of severance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a bold decision for the country and the nation to take practical measures to recognize and respect each other's ideology and system. The south Korean authorities should respond to the call of the times and history by taking practical measures for the radical improvement of the inter-Korean relations as early as possible.

National Sports Contests of Workers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- The 6th National Sports Contests of Workers took place in Pyongyang from April 26 to May 3.
 They involved football and defense sports games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers competing in the games well displayed their sports technique, collectivist spirit and noble mental and moral traits they had cultivated in the fruitful efforts to build an economic power under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 The closing ceremony was held at the Badminton Gymnasium in Chongchun Street on May 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prize banners, citations and medals were awarded to units that distinguished themselves in the games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, in his closing address called upon all the sectors and units to intensify mass sports activities in the future, thus contributing to the all-round preparations of all the people for labor and national defense and enrichment of the cultural and emotional life of working people as required by the Songun era.

Rodong Sinmun Observes Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday dedicates an article to the 15th anniversary of the publication of leader Kim Jong Il's work "Our Socialism Centered on the Masses Shall Not Perish".
 The work, published on May 5, Juche 80 (1991), is a highly important work as it comprehensively clarifies the essential nature, advantages and invincibility of Korean-style socialism, the article says. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il authored this work at a time when such tragedy as the frustration of the socialist cause took place in various Eastern European countries due to the persistent anti-socialist moves of the imperialists and opportunists. Through this he scientifically proved that socialism is sure to triumph and instilled firm conviction of sure victory in socialism into the revolutionary people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work serves as important guidelines to be always held fast to in accomplishing the socialist cause in our times as it clarifies the solidity and invincibility of socialism centred on the masses which puts the people forward as a genuine master of society and makes everything serve them, it says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, among other things, serves as precious guidelines indicating the way of consolidating the ideological foundation of socialism and victoriously advancing the people's cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il in the work taught that Korean-style socialism was built and has grown stronger, guided by the Juche idea. He scientifically proved that the above-said socialism remains solid and invincible as it makes it possible to protect and fully meet the wishes and interests of the people as required by the Juche idea.
 The work serves as an ever-lasting banner for remarkably bolstering the driving force of socialism to advance the socialist cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il in the work teaches that the people are the driving force advancing the socialist society but they can creditably fulfill their role as an independent driving force of the revolution and successfully build socialism only when they are united around the Party and the leader as firm as a rock. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The singled-minded unity in the DPRK with the headquarters of the revolution at its core provides a sure guarantee for all victories of Songun Korea.

Edible Pigments Good for Health Made
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- Scientists of the Food and Fermentation Institutes of the Branch Academy of Light Industry Science under the State Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have recently made edible pigments beneficial to health.
 They made edible natural red pigments by treating Beta Vulgaris var. rubra and red rice by the microorganism culture method. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The edible pigments can be used to give red color to foodstuffs including confectionery, soft drinks, processed meats and peppered bean paste and medicines. And they are harmless and antibiotic in the human body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Beta Vulgaris var. rubra is effective for the treatment and prevention of digestive diseases including gastritis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Red rice helps digestion in the human body, reduces cholesterol in blood and prevents cancer. And it makes complexion smooth.

Indonesian Embassy Officials Help Korean Peasants
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 4 (KCNA) -- Charge d'Affaires ad Interim Bambang Irawan K. and staff members of the Indonesian embassy here visited the DPRK-Indonesia Friendship Yaksu Co-op Farm on Thursday to help its peasants in farming.
 After going round the room dedicated to the introduction of the farm history, the visitors transplanted humus-potted maize seedlings together with farmers.
 During a break they sang songs of the two countries and talked with the farmers, deepening friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The charge d'affaires said that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries are growing stronger and wished the farmers greater success in the agricultural production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The staff members of the embassy conveyed aid materials to the farm.
